FAQ.banner.title: FAQ
FAQ.gettingStarted.title: Getting started
FAQ.gettingStarted.0.answer: We support any government-issued ID from any country, as long as the alphabet is in latin characters (For example, we do not support arabic, korean or chinese).
FAQ.gettingStarted.0.question: What documents are supported by Mati?
FAQ.gettingStarted.1.answer: We support every country in the world. You can customize and restrict the specific countries or regions you want to work with from your Mati dashboard.
FAQ.gettingStarted.1.question: What countries does Mati provide coverage for?
FAQ.gettingStarted.2.answer: Yes. After configuring the document requirements on your Mati dashboard, select all the optional documents. Now the user can choose between multiple documents such as a passport, national ID or driver's license.
FAQ.gettingStarted.2.question: Can users choose between multiple documents?
FAQ.gettingStarted.3.answer.1: Mati lets you create as many verification flows as you need, so that you can integrate in different places within your website or App. Each verification flow can have its specific configuration and name.
FAQ.gettingStarted.3.answer.2: For example, let’s say you accept users from the USA and the UK and for some reason, you can only accept driving licences from USA users, and passports from UK users. With Mati’s multi verification flows, you can create two verification flows for your regional requirements/variations.
FAQ.gettingStarted.3.question: When should I use multiple verification flows?
FAQ.gettingStarted.4.answer: Mati only charges verifications that users complete. If a user only completed half of the Mati verification flow we will not charge you.
FAQ.gettingStarted.4.question: When am I charged for a verification?
FAQ.gettingStarted.5.answer.1: {verified}. The verification passed every check that you configured on your dashboard (document requirements, biometrics requirements, additional checks, etc...).
FAQ.gettingStarted.5.answer.2: {manualReviewNeeded}. This occurs when Mati flags something unusual with a verification. This may happen for various reasons such as fake ID, watchlist flag and failing face match. Since our customers' business rules and use cases differ, we allow you, the customer, to take the final decisions of accepting/rejecting the user.
FAQ.gettingStarted.5.question: What are possible outcomes of a Mati verification?
FAQ.gettingStarted.6.answer: No, we do not reject users. When we detect something wrong, we mark the user as “‘Manual Review Needed” on your dashboard. If this occurs, you can reject this user or request additional information.
FAQ.gettingStarted.6.question: Does Mati reject users?
FAQ.gettingStarted.7.answer.1: Yes. To restrict and edit permissions please follow these instructions:
FAQ.gettingStarted.7.answer.2: 1) Go to the ‘Account’ section of the dashboard.
FAQ.gettingStarted.7.answer.4: 3) Make any changes to the listed members in the roles column by selecting either admin or verification agent.
FAQ.gettingStarted.7.answer.6: full permission to all Mati dashboard
FAQ.gettingStarted.7.answer.8: only access to the ‘Verification List’ section of the dashboard. These users will not be able to change any Mati settings.
FAQ.gettingStarted.7.question: How can I give restricted permissions to my Mati dashboard?
FAQ.technicalIntegration.title: Technical integration
FAQ.technicalIntegration.0.answer: It depends on your business needs. An SDK is the easiest way to integrate Mati, and we have spent years optimizing the conversion rates. If you need or want to customize your frontend (UI/UX), then an API would be a better fit.
FAQ.technicalIntegration.0.question: Should I integrate Mati API or Mati SDKs?
FAQ.technicalIntegration.1.answer: Webhooks are optional but they allow you to connect Mati’s backend with your backend to automate the verification flow inside your App logic. That way you eliminate the need to manually review each verification on our dashboard. To hook up the webhooks, set the endpoint at the bottom of the Integration tab, in the “Webhook URL and Secret” section.
FAQ.technicalIntegration.1.question: What are “webhooks” and how are they related to my verifications?
FAQ.technicalIntegration.footer: Learn more about our webhooks inside {docsLink}
FAQ.securityCompliance.title: Security & compliance
FAQ.securityCompliance.0.answer.1: To ensure authenticity, Mati performs two checks, (1) Alteration detection and (2) Template matching.
FAQ.securityCompliance.0.answer.2: Alteration detection is a requirement in every verification we process. Alteration detection ensures documents look visually official, contain the right watermarks, the right structure, and have the correct fields. If the document was altered in any way (image modification, text modification, watermark modification), Mati will detect it and flag the user for you.
FAQ.securityCompliance.0.answer.3: Template matching will check that the document is from the correct country. If a user uploads a driver’s licence instead of a passport, or a Swiss national ID instead of a French one, the user will be flagged and you will be alerted.
FAQ.securityCompliance.0.question: What checks does Mati perform to verify a document’s authenticity?
FAQ.securityCompliance.1.answer: If this happens, you should ask the user to go through the verification process again, or try to connect to the government website directly.
FAQ.securityCompliance.1.question: What happens if a verification comes back with an error in a  government check?
FAQ.securityCompliance.2.table.1.1: Australian Government Dept. of Foreign Trade & Affairs Sanctions Lists
FAQ.securityCompliance.2.question: Which watchlists are included by default in my Mati verifications?
FAQ.securityCompliance.3.answer: All data is encrypted using AES-256. This includes user selfies, videos, document images, and any verification data.
FAQ.securityCompliance.3.question: Does Mati encrypt the data?
FAQ.securityCompliance.4.answer: Mati uses Amazon (AWS) as our servers. We have multiple server locations around the globe (in the USA and in the European Union) to make sure we comply with local regulations like GDPR.
FAQ.securityCompliance.4.question: Where does Mati store verification data?
FAQ.securityCompliance.5.answer: Yes. If you enable this feature, your data will be erased from both your dashboard and Mati’s servers.
FAQ.securityCompliance.5.question: Does the “GDPR setting” delete all data from Mati servers and my Mati  dashboard?

DocumentationSection.title: Mati Documentation
DocumentationSection.description: We work hard for the integration to be quick. Generally, it takes a few minutes to integrate our SDKs and a couple of hours to integrate our webhook.
ApiSection.title: API
ApiSection.description: Do you have a case of special use and cannot integrate our SDKs? We have an API for that!
WebSDKSection.title: Web SDK
WebSDKSection.description: Integrate our web SDK in seconds into any website. Optimized for desktop and mobile.
MobileSDKSection.title: Mobile SDKs
MobileSDKSection.description: If you have native or hybrid apps, our mobile SDKs are here for you. The integration takes some lines of code.
PermalinkSection.title: Direct Verification Link
PermalinkSection.description: Send that link to verify users via SMS, e-mail, intercom or in any other way. It's always the simplest way to get started!
WebhookDocumentationSection.title: Webhook Documentation
WebhookDocumentationSection.description: Mati transmits all the information of check of the user via a webhook insurance, directly to your backend.
WebhookSection.title: Webhook URL and secret
WebhookSection.description: Enter a webhook URL where Mati will send the user's verification data after each verification. The secret will be used to secure the webhook.
